subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Male imago: 1) general coloration: thorax orangish brown, abdomen grayish brown (
Fig. 19
); 2) forewing with two costal cross veins basal to bulla; 3) hind wing with costal projection well developed, forming an acute angle, located approximately 2/3 distance from base to apex of wing; 4) abdominal segments II–V with translucent white basal bands (
Fig. 19
); 5) penis projection spine-like, long and anteriorly directed (
Fig. 38
); 6) penis lobes fused on basal ⅓ (
Fig. 38
); 7) ventral region of penis lobes without a well-marked sclerotized region (
Fig. 38
). Adapted from 
Traver (1947)
.
